在'''美国'''，自20世紀以来，'''[[种族|种族]]与[[犯罪|犯罪]]之间的关系'''一直是公众和学术關注的焦點<ref>Gabbidon & Greene (2005a:ix-x); Gabbidon & Greene (2005b:37).</ref>。不同种族群体之间的犯罪率差异很大。在美国，大多数兇殺案的[[受害者|受害者]]与犯罪者属于[[黑人|黑人]]。

学术研究表明，在刑事案件中，一些少数族裔的比例过高，部分原因在于社会经济因素，如贫困、沒有受到良好教育以及接触有害化学品（例如[[鉛|鉛]]）和污染等因素<ref name=":5">{{Cite journal|title=Urban Black Violence: The Effect of Male Joblessness and Family Disruption|url=http://nrs.harvard.edu/urn-3:HUL.InstRepos:3226953|last=Sampson, Robert J.|date=September 1987|journal=American Journal of Sociology|issue=2|doi=10.1086/228748|volume=93|pages=348–382|jstor=2779588}}</ref><ref name=":6">{{Cite journal|title=Social Anatomy of Racial and Ethnic Disparities in Violence|url=https://archive.org/details/sim_american-journal-of-public-health_2005-02_95_2/page/224|last=Sampson|first=Robert J.|last2=Morenoff|first2=Jeffrey D.|date=February 2005|journal=American Journal of Public Health|issue=2|doi=10.2105/AJPH.2004.037705|volume=95|pages=224–232|pmc=1449156|pmid=15671454|last3=Raudenbush|first3=Stephen}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=An updated lead-crime roundup for 2018|url=https://www.motherjones.com/kevin-drum/2018/02/an-updated-lead-crime-roundup-for-2018/|accessdate=2021-02-20|author=Drum|first=Kevin|work=Mother Jones|language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|title=Serious Crime in Urban Neighborhoods: Is There a Race Effect?|url=https://doi.org/10.1080/02732170490459502|last=Shihadeh|first=Edward S.|last2=Shrum|first2=Wesley|date=2004-07-01|journal=Sociological Spectrum|issue=4|doi=10.1080/02732170490459502|volume=24|pages=507–533|issn=0273-2173}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|title=Does Age or Poverty Level Best Predict Criminal Arrest and Homicide Rates? A Preliminary Investigation|url=https://www.semanticscholar.org/paper/Does-Age-or-Poverty-Level-Best-Predict-Criminal-and-Brown-Males/3864dd48d646ee7c3a2169bce093a9bd8b6d4287|last=Brown|first=Elizabeth|last2=Males|first2=Mike A.|date=2011|accessdate=2021-02-20|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|title=Explaining the Gaps in White, Black, and Hispanic Violence since 1990: Accounting for Immigration, Incarceration, and Inequality|url=https://doi.org/10.1177/0003122416635667|last=Light|first=Michael T.|last2=Ulmer|first2=Jeffery T.|date=2016-04-01|journal=American Sociological Review|issue=2|doi=10.1177/0003122416635667|volume=81|pages=290–315|language=en|issn=0003-1224}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|title=Racial and Ethnic Disparities in Structural Disadvantage and Crime: White, Black, and Hispanic Comparisons*|url=https://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/abs/10.1111/j.1540-6237.2012.00868.x|last=Ulmer|first=Jeffery T.|last2=Harris|first2=Casey T.|date=2012|journal=Social Science Quarterly|issue=3|doi=10.1111/j.1540-6237.2012.00868.x|volume=93|pages=799–819|language=en|issn=1540-6237|pmc=4097310|pmid=25035523|last3=Steffensmeier|first3=Darrell}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|title=The Structural Context of Homicide: Accounting for Racial Differences in Process|url=https://www.jstor.org/stable/2657382|last=Krivo|first=Lauren J.|last2=Peterson|first2=Ruth D.|date=2000|journal=American Sociological Review|issue=4|doi=10.2307/2657382|volume=65|pages=547–559|issn=0003-1224|jstor=2657382}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|title=Understanding international crime trends: The legacy of preschool lead exposure|url=https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S0013935107000503|last=Nevin|first=Rick|date=2007-07-01|journal=Environmental Research|issue=3|doi=10.1016/j.envres.2007.02.008|volume=104|pages=315–336|language=en|bibcode=2007ER....104..315N|issn=0013-9351|pmid=17451672}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|title=The intersection of aggregate-level lead exposure and crime|url=https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S0013935116301037|last=Boutwell|first=Brian B.|last2=Nelson|first2=Erik J.|date=2016-07-01|journal=Environmental Research|doi=10.1016/j.envres.2016.03.023|volume=148|pages=79–85|language=en|bibcode=2016ER....148...79B|issn=0013-9351|pmid=27035924|last3=Emo|first3=Brett|last4=Vaughn|first4=Michael G.|last5=Schootman|first5=Mario|last6=Rosenfeld|first6=Richard|last7=Lewis|first7=Roger}}</ref>。與[[种族隔离|种族隔离]]有關的居住隔離也与犯罪率的种族差异有关，因为黑人歷史上長期被政府和私人阻止迁入繁荣的低犯罪率地区 <ref>{{Cite journal|title=Crime and segregation|url=http://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S0167268107001357|last=O’Flaherty|first=Brendan|last2=Sethi|first2=Rajiv|date=November 1, 2007|journal=Journal of Economic Behavior & Organization|issue=3|doi=10.1016/j.jebo.2006.07.005|volume=64|pages=391–405|language=en|issn=0167-2681}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|title=Segregation and Crime: The Effect of Black Social Isolation on the Rates of Black Urban Violence|url=https://academic.oup.com/sf/article/74/4/1325/2233401|last=Shihadeh|first=Edward S.|last2=Flynn|first2=Nicole|date=June 1, 1996|journal=Social Forces|issue=4|doi=10.1093/sf/74.4.1325|volume=74|pages=1325–1352|language=en|issn=0037-7732}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|title=The Effects of Racial/Ethnic Segregation on Latino and Black Homicide|last=Feldmeyer|first=Ben|date=September 1, 2010|journal=The Sociological Quarterly|issue=4|doi=10.1111/j.1533-8525.2010.01185.x|volume=51|pages=600–623|issn=0038-0253|pmid=20939127}}</ref>。

